      • NMSPacketReflection

        public NMSPacketReflection(java.lang.String packetName,
                           @Nullable
                           java.lang.Object... args)
        For reflecting NMS packets
        Parameters:
        packetName - is the name of the packet you are reflecting although special packets have separate classes These classes are NMSScoreboardTeamPacketReflection, NMSEntityDestroyPacketReflection, NMSPlayerInfoPacketReflection NMSEntityPacketReflection NMSNamedEntitySpawnPacketReflection
        args - these are the arguments that the packet would normally take. If you use the wrong class there will be an error and the server will crash (For example you use a float instead of a byte) MAKE SURE TO CAST!! IMPORTANT NOTE: Passing nulls into this will not work if you have something null you wish to pass in to the constructor please use a different NMS Packet Reflection constructor.

                           java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Class<?>,java.lang.Integer> specialClassForObject,
                           java.lang.Object... args)
        Parameters:
        packetName - The name of the packet to reflect
        specialClassForObject - A hashmap of a Class and object where the class is the class type for a constructor and the object being the value.
        See Also:
        to see how this would work, as well for another example

      • NMSPacketReflection

        public NMSPacketReflection(java.lang.String packetName,
                           java.lang.Class<?>[] classes,
                           java.lang.Object... args)
        Parameters:
        packetName - The name of the packet to reflect
        classes - List of all classes that this packet's constructor uses. They are in the order that they appear in the wanted constructor.
        args - List of arguments to fill into the constructor. (In the order they appear in the constructor)
